The paper proposes a novel model for temporal detection and localization using deep neural networks with weak supervision. The model is validated in experiments involving audio and image data, indicating potential relevance to sub-categories such as cs.SD (Sound), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
